 McLaren promise a fair finale
London: McLaren have ruled out any favouritism in next weeks Formula One title showdown in Brazil between Lewis Hamilton and teammate Fernando Alonso. The team wants to make it absolutely clear that its policy of treating both Fernando and Lewis with complete equality and fairness will continue for the final race, McLaren said on their website. McLaren and Mercedes-Benz will continue to take every step that is within their control to ensure that both Fernando and Lewis will enjoy the same opportunity to win in terms of equality of car, engine, tactics and use of resources. Hamilton leads Alonso by four points ahead of the title decider on October 21. Spaniard Alonso is three points ahead of Kimi Raikkonen in the sports first three-way finale since 1986.  (REUTERS) 
